title: For Sale:  Airsoft Starter Kit
postcontent:
I have for sale some Airsoft guns and stuff to get you started. First, we have the full/semi-auto AK-47. It features a full metal front and bolt cover, all steel gears, a folding stock, adjustable front and rear sights, 2 high cap mags(about 500-600rds per), front grip, and battery and charger. This thing is a beast!! I have a real AK-47 and the weight and feel of this Airsoft version is dead on. It's very accurate even at a good distance. It says 495fps but we chronographed it at 405 with 20gram bbs. 
Next is the Taurus PT 24/7. It's a spring loaded pistol. It has one mag that holds 25 bbs. The gun it's self is rather light, but once you put the mag in it heavies it up and then feels realistic. It says 315fps but we didn't test this one. It's fairly accurate at close range, but it is only spring loaded and not Co2, so it doesn't have the distance. It's a great little side arm to go with the AK though. (p.s. it fits nicely in my plastic Springfield XD belt holster). Also with the pistol, I have an airsoft speed loader. holds something like 100bbs and pumps out 4-5bbs per squeeze. The speed loader also has the attachment piece to plug into the high cap rifle mags. It's a handy little tool.
Then there's the face mask. It's all one piece, goggles aren't removable. They also aren't scratched up, just a tad dirty. The mask wraps around your head to cover the ears. The inside has the nice foam padding for comfort and a good seal. 
And finally, the bag of bbs. they're 20 gram, ultra slick competition grade bbs. Never had a feed issue with these at all. there are probably 4,000 left in the bag.
Now all these things have only been used once. My buddies and I had a Zombie Apocalypse Day in the woods. It was a lot of fun. Unfortunately, I am now in a position of needing the money more than the fun. Always a sad realization to have. lol. All in all, it's a great deal and it's so much fun. You will be very happy with everything. So please, call or text me if you are interested. I am looking for $250 for everything. Thanks for looking.

Brian REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Professional DuraCoat Finishing
postcontent:
DuraCoat will protect your gear for a lifetime of worry free easy maintenance, it looks awesome, and once fully cured it is tough as nails! Make your gear the color or pattern you want for far less than the cost of buying a "wrapped" weapon. Wrapping or hydro dipping does not have the durability or the protection that DuraCoat offers many times over. 

 Do you have something that sticks out like a sore thumb in the woods? Or something you just want to make the color or colors you prefer? Do you want your item to be one of a kind, protected forever and the color or color combination you want it? I'm your man.

I offer sandblasting, refinishing, and restoration for your hunting and shooting gear. If you have an item that has seen wear and tear, is blemished, or pitted with rust I can make it new again. Maybe it's just old and is needing to be refinished, and you want a quality, professional job done please feel free to contact me. Make sure your gear is protected forever, invisible to wary eyes and impervious to the elements DuraCoat it. 

Cleaning is done in no time with DuraCoat. Simply wipe it with a damp rag and you're done. Or leave it, that's fine too, a little dirt will help you blend in when you head back into the great outdoors. 

I can camouflage anything and specialize in application of DuraCoat which is an extremely durable and excellent two part epoxy finish. If you'd like to see all the available colors you can check it by googling Lauer Weaponry or by going to this webpage http://lauerweaponry.com/   

I can do binoculars, bipods, range finders, magazines, helmets, comm gear, stocks, barrels, scopes and bases / rings and anything else that needs to blend in to complete your camouflage breakup or just needs a new finish.

Patterns include digital, multicam, tiger stripe,  woodland, shadow grass, winter twig, brush, and on and on. In any color combination you like. You tell me what you want, and I'll make it happen. 

Price will vary with time and supplies required to make your gear and items one of a kind. I cut my own painting camouflage patterns on a CNC stencil machine in order to give you the professional look you want. I also have been seen on the farm picking through natural items to use as templates. I can add artwork, initials, quotes, etc to your gear as well. No vinyl, no "wraps or dips," just diamond hard yet flexible DuraCoat. 

My work is top notch and second to none. I can and will provide references if you'd like. I have over a decade of experience in the application of finishing systems and will ensure that what you want is what you get and that it will last a lifetime and be something you love to pick up and look at, take to the field, or show your friends. 

I have been painting for 16 years and have been to many Military Technical Schools involving paint systems, preparation, methods, and application. I have been into shooting sports my whole life and I truly love seeing my work and the looks on people's faces when I return their gear to them fully customized.  

If you're interested or just have any questions feel free to e-mail me at REDACTED or call me at REDACTED. 
Thank you for your time and interest.

"It is better to live one day as a lion, than a thousand days a lamb."

title: For Sale:  COP 357 Derringer *Rare*
location: Boca Raton, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent: The COP 357 is an extremely rare pistol that is no longer in production. Made famous in the movie "Blade Runner" and seen in such movies as "Bad Boys", "The Matrix Reloaded",and most recently "21 Jump Street" the COP would be a welcomed piece to any collectors collection, Or just for anyone looking for something rare, beautiful, and different. Easy to fire and easy on the eyes this rare pistol has 4 barrels which fire 357 magnums or .38 specials. The COP 357 is a 4 shot Derringer type pistol chambered for the powerful .357 Magnum round. It was designed by Robert Hillberg, based on his earlier work on the Hillberg Insurgency Weapon. It was manufactured by the now defunct COP Inc. of 3040 West Lomita Blvd., Torrance, California (COP stood for Compact Off-Duty Police). The double action weapon is about twice as wide, and substantially heavier than the typical .25 automatic pistol, though its relatively compact size and powerful cartridge made it a good choice for a defensive weapon or a police backup gun. The COP 357 is quite robust in design and construction. It is made of solid stainless steel components. Cartridges are loaded into the four separate chambers by sliding a latch that "pops-up" the barrel for loading purposes, similar to top-break shotguns. Each of the four chambers has its own dedicated firing pin. It uses an internal hammer, which is activated by depressing the trigger to hit a ratcheting/rotating striker that in turn strikes one firing pin at a time. Older "pepperboxes" also used multiple barrels, but the barrels were the part that rotated. The COP 357 operates similarly to the Sharps rimfire pepperbox of the 1850s, in that it uses the ratcheting/rotating striker, which is completely internal, to fire each chamber in sequence. Any questions please feel free to message me. Good luck to all bidders and an early congrats to whoever wins!

title: For Sale:  Intratec Tec-22 (All Models) Firing Pin and Rebound Spring
location: Northwest Indiana   Lake County   Dyer, Indiana, United States
postcontent:
The firing pin in the Intratec Tec-22 firearms break frequently. The rebound spring is often lost or bent and is not useable. We have found the cause of the breaking to be "SHEAR STRESS". The stress is the result of the design of the bolt. The design of the bolt's can't be changed, so we zeroed in on the material used in the manufacture of the firing pins. We made firing pin's from several kinds of steel, including hardened A2 tool steel. That didn't work. We heat treated pin's to different hardness's. That didn't work! We even went so far as to have a batch of firing pins made of Titanium. Much to our engineer's surprise, that batch broke even faster than the pin's made from steel. postcontent:
The flechette round carries about 24, 1 inch dart shaped projectiles. In Vietnam they were used in taking out snipers hiding in thick brush or trees. Due to the penetration of these projectiles, tree limbs and brush will not disperse the darts as readily as round shot. They will give an all covering pattern within trees or brush. This round is a 2 3/4" hull and will fit in all modern 20 Gauges. Not intended for hunting.  These rounds are illegal in several jurisdictions including but not limited to FL, MA, IL, HI, AK, DC and NYC.

title: For Sale:  Winchester model 63, 1934 Rare 20" barrel
postcontent: Unbelieveabley fine condition, this model 63's serial number of 2948 indicates via Winchester's on-line records that it was manufactured in the first quarter of 1934, the 2nd year of manufacture for the model 63. Additionally, this gun has a 20 inch barrel, which was only offered during the first 3 years, making it an even more rare collectible. I am offering this gun at auction at far less than gun book value because I have decided to retire overseas and will have no use for it. In my opinion, the bluing and wood on this gun are easily at 95%. There is a little bluing wear from carrying at the action shoulders and it also has a small amount of typical muzzel wear. The bore is excellent. The straight grained walnut is beautiful without checks, cracks, or even noticeable wear.

The LT104 is the best mount made for attaching high-power riflescopes onto flattop-style AR15's, period.

The LT104 places the centerline of the optic 1.5" above the top of the rail for optimum cheek weld with a variety of AR-platform rifles.
